A technical not on uniformizing the IO code during learning in the cerrebellum. What does that mean. It mean that The IO should have during trajectories for every trajectories each units having a fixed activity at any point in time. This activity correspond to the spontaneous activity of IO cells balancing the constant parrallel fibers potentition, that we don't simulate here as it is part of the biologically realistic backpropagation process that we skip. For the computational model we can even do something not very biorealistic but elegant which would be to have bipolar tranfer function in the IO neurons such as tangent and to aim 0 activity. This bipolar tranfer function will avoid the trivial solution of over inhibiting the IO as this would be punished by negative activity when DCN code change. But I guess if we follow this path all neurons in the model should have bipolar transfer function for it to behave well.

